@NextDevBoard could you please add an example pipeline that we can run?

From what I see, https://github.com/apache/beam/pull/2555 is required to make the Cloud Spanner client work.

Otherwise I'm getting runtime errors. Cloud Spanner uses `com.google.rpc.LocalizedMessage` which not available in `grpc-google-common-protos.version` 0.1.0.

LGTM on my end.
Dataflow tests are broken for about a week now.
@bjchambers - All good?

@JingsongLi 

I rebased your work on top of the (very) recent Splittable DoFn and Flink module reorganisation changes: https://github.com/aljoscha/beam/commits/finish-pr-2300-flink-metrics

I also tried a different approach for the source metrics. I didn't like all the `getDelegate()` methods to much so I changed it into an invocation util. I still don't like that we have special invoke calls, though. What do you think?

LGTM
[Build 9696](https://builds.apache.org/job/beam_PreCommit_Java_MavenInstall/9696/) was finished successfully. 

@davorbonaci  please help with the merge.
